The goal of this project is to create an app that uses a database to organize recipes in a smarter way. 
Instead of just storing recipes as plain text, this app connects ingredients like a network, or a “food graph.” 
Each ingredient is stored on its own with details about it, which makes the app more powerful than a basic cookbook.

One important feature is a “Smart Swap” tool. 
This helps suggest ingredient substitutes if someone has allergies, special diets, or is missing something in their kitchen.

The app uses a database structure that can handle many recipes and ingredients at the same time, 
since one recipe can have many ingredients and one ingredient can be used in many recipes. 
It also tracks flavors like “umami” or “zesty” to help organize and search recipes better.

Because everything is connected, the data stays accurate. 
For example, if an ingredient is marked as an allergen, every recipe that uses it will update automatically. 
In the end, this project shows how a well-organized database can solve real problems, 
like converting measurements and helping users quickly find the right recipes.
